Studies in Texas and Louisiana marshes have demonstrated that production is related to temperature, salinity, and access to emergent marsh vegetation.  We are currently developing a systems model that will simulate recruitment, growth, and emigration of brown shrimp. This data will be used to help validate the model</abstract>       <purpose>The goal of this study is to examine the effects of differing temperature, salinity, and marsh surface flooding regimes on brown shrimp growth and mortality rates</purpose>       <notes/>       <supplemental-info/>       <is-display-xml-formats>Y</is-display-xml-formats>       <data-status>In Work</data-status>
